& [SourceSet] is proof_system_context
  + [source_001] is https://www.jair.org/index.php/jair/article/download/10392/24888/19250
    = title: Towards Understanding and Harnessing the Potential of Clause Learning
    = extracted_boundary: clause learning is studied relative to resolution proof systems and can be compared by proof-size strength
  + [source_002] is https://arxiv.org/pdf/1401.3868
    = title: Clause-Learning Algorithms with Many Restarts and Bounded-Width Resolution
    = extracted_boundary: clause learning with restarts can detect unsatisfiability from bounded-width resolution refutations under stated algorithmic conditions, but this remains bounded by the needed refutation width and conflict budget
  + [source_003] is https://cdn.aaai.org/AAAI/2008/AAAI08-045.pdf
    = title: Clause Learning Can Effectively P-Simulate General Propositional Resolution
    = extracted_boundary: stronger clause-learning frameworks may p-simulate general resolution, but that places the route inside resolution-strength proof complexity rather than solving P versus NP by itself

